I"ô<p>Cablegram [377 [1] LONDON, n.d. [1 September 1939], 2.20 p.m.</p>

<p>FOR PRIME MINISTER MOST SECRET</p>

<p>Cabinet just risen. Decision immediate ultimatum to Germany without time limit as soon as action concerted with French with whom Secretary for Foreign Affairs [2] now getting in touch. Ciano [3] has given assurances Italy not participating.</p>

<p>Parliament meeting 6. Dominions Office cables now being cyphered giving above and additional information.</p>

<p>BRUCE</p>

<p>_</p>

